#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/mia/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/js-hoist-regexp.md
M|rules|title: Hoist RegExp Creation
M|rules|impact: LOW-MEDIUM
M|rules|impactDescription: avoids recreation
M|rules|tags: javascript, regexp, optimization, memoization
M|rules|Don't create RegExp inside render. Hoist to module scope or memoize with `useMemo()`.
M|rules|**Incorrect (new RegExp every render):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|function Highlighter({ text, query }: Props) {
M|rules|const regex = new RegExp(`(${query})`, 'gi')
M|rules|const parts = text.split(regex)
M|rules|return <>{parts.map((part, i) => ...)}</>
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (memoize or hoist):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|const EMAIL_REGEX = /^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$/
M|rules|function Highlighter({ text, query }: Props) {
M|rules|const regex = useMemo(
M|rules|() => new RegExp(`(${escapeRegex(query)})`, 'gi'),
M|rules|[query]
M|rules|)
M|rules|const parts = text.split(regex)
M|rules|return <>{parts.map((part, i) => ...)}</>
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Warning (global regex has mutable state):**
M|rules|Global regex (`/g`) has mutable `lastIndex` state:
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|const regex = /foo/g
M|rules|regex.test('foo')  // true, lastIndex = 3
M|rules|regex.test('foo')  // false, lastIndex = 0
M|rules|```